description.narrative:
The Project Preparation Facility (PPF) initiative started in 2017 with an initial end date of December of 2021 and comprises of support to a total of seven studies, namely:
1. Tsate HPP (Hydro Power Plant) Environmental and Social Impact Assesment (ESIA) snd Resettlement Action Plan (RAP);
2. Development of a Project Document with business case for replacement of incandescent lamps with LEDs;
3. Feasibility study for transmission grid extension;
4. Tsate power plant transmission line and accsess road project;
5. Project identification studies for Lot 1 - HPPs and Lot 2 - Photovoltaic off.grid;
6. Feasibility studies for the rehabilitation of Nampula, Xai Xai and Angoche distribution networks;
7. Massinga Vilanculos ESIA.
Due to the long delay in the procurement process especially in the approval of the contracts by the relevant Mozambican authorities that is the Tribunal Administrativo and the ministry of finance there was consequently very long delays in initiating the works with the first kick off meeting being held for contract number 1 above in July of 2020. The rest of the contracts had their kick off meetings between August and December of 2020 and site visits were also further delayed due to the covid-19 pandemic hence no significant progress had been made  with the exception of two projects, that is, the Development of a project document with business case  for replacement if incandescent lamps with LEDs whose inception report was approved by EDM in December 2020. The second project is the Feasibility study for transmission line and grid extension where the site visit was held in November 2020 and the inception report will be submitted in the first quarter of 2021. 
On a more positive note the German bank KfW is actively involved in the Tsate HPP ESIA since it has shown interest in financing the construction of the power plant in the event that the study being currently financed by the Swedish government gives positive results.
